## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Spleen deficiency with dampness accumulation
**Key Symptoms**: Abdominal distension, poor appetite, nausea, feeling of fullness after eating, loose stools, heavy sensation in body and limbs, mental fogginess
**Tongue**: Thick white greasy coating
**Pulse**: Slow and slippery

### Secondary Applications
- Chronic gastritis with dampness
- Functional dyspepsia
- Chronic diarrhea from dampness
- Chronic fatigue with dampness constitution
- Seasonal affective disorder (dampness type)
- Chronic sinusitis with thick discharge

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Functional dyspepsia and gastroparesis
- Chronic gastritis and peptic ulcers
- Irritable bowel syndrome (dampness type)
- Chronic fatigue syndrome with digestive symptoms
- Seasonal depression with dampness
- Chronic rhinosinusitis

## üìù Therapeutic Actions
